                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/448a Suppl.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flexer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 9, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Department’s telegram No. 65, October 25, noon. Has the Legation been
                    approached by Panamanian authorities with a view to discussing the points listed
                    in the Department’s telegram referring to sales to ships? If so, please
                    telegraph substance of any such discussions and forward complete report by
                    airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
